9:57 AM CO: RMW , REP: Melstrom, CLERK: Lindabaur. Prosecuting attorney Aaron M. Damrau in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Dennis Raymond Welter in court, in custody.  Attorney Shirlene Renee Perrin in court for Dennis Raymond Welter. Court notes Pretrial Assessment Report filed. Atty Perrin argues bond modification. Atty Perrin states DE cannot post cash bond and is also in need of medical treatment. ADA Damrau responds and objects to modification. Court questions attys. Atty Perrin states warrant is still active in Chippewa County, but anticipates a bond hearing in that matter. Atty Perrin isn't certain about the outstanding Ramsey County Warrant, but believes there is an open Ramsey County case. Defendant states he doesn't have a warrant in Ramsey County. Atty Perrin confirms there is not an active warrant in Ramsey County, MN. Court services advises that DE has a warrant in Wright County, MN, but it's not extraditable. Atty Perrin states DE is not aware of anything in Wright County, MN. Court denies bond modification motion. Atty Perrin invokes speedy trial demand. Court sets 2 day Jury Trial and FPT. Trial submissions due 11/30/22- Court will issue a scheduling order. Court advises Defendant of right to speedy trial demand and scheduled JT outside of speedy trial demand window. Court finds limited waiver of right to speedy trial. Adjourned at 10:24 AM.  gll

It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, S.B.P. or D.M.L.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

I understand that I must report to and comply with all terms, conditions, and protocols of the St. Croix County Justice Support Center. I further understand that I am required to be fitted with a GPS monitoring device and cannot be within .5 miles of S.B.P.'s residence. Failure to report and/or comply with conditions and/or protocols may result in a report to the District Attorney's Office, an arrest warrant, and/or referral for criminal charges.

I understand that I must IMMEDIATELY report to the Justice Support Center located adjacent to the lower parking lot of the St. Croix County Government Center. 

If after regular business hours I must call (715)245-4109 to schedule an appointment with the Justice Support Center by the end of the following business day. 

If the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bail jumping.
